Fernando is in Istanbul.
Brazilian footballer Fernando Francisco Reges, with whom Galatasaray Club has started transfer negotiations, has arrived in Istanbul.
The Brazilian footballer arrived at Atatürk Airport and was greeted enthusiastically by fans.
Fernando left the airport to the cheers and affection of the yellow and red fans, who were waiting for him in a special vehicle under security measures.
Thirty-year-old Fernando, who started his career with Brazil's Vila Nova and played for Estrela Amadora, Porto and Manchester City, plays in midfield.
The Brazilian footballer is expected to sign a contract with the yellow and red team after passing a medical examination.
Galatasaray, which continues the transfer work, has reached an agreement with Manchester City for 5 million 250 thousand Euros for Fernando, who has been trying to join his squad for a long time.
Flash from the U.S. move on Raqqa:
