"The Raqqa Internal Security Force, composed mostly of Arabs and local anti-Daesh volunteers, continues to maintain order in the cleared areas of the city and prevent terrorists from escaping or returning", Dillon said.
This week, 230 more people have completed their training and joined the group, Dillon said, adding that "the current strength is 850".
