The most important lesson that our Ottoman past imparted to the Republic was the fact that the rapid perception of world conjuncture and change was an inevitable prerequisite for survival.
Because this lesson has been absorbed so well, we have been able to be a model country of this geography that has managed to preserve its unity, integrity, stability in peace from World War I until today.
