Italy has warned NGOs operating migrant rescue boats in the Mediterranean that they will not be allowed to continue if they do not comply with new rules affecting their operations.
"If NGOs do not comply with the new statute, it will be difficult to see them continue to operate", Interior Minister Marco Minniti said in an interview with the Turin newspaper La Stampa.
Minniti's warning came a day after Italian authorities seized a boat operated by the German charity Jugend Rettet on suspicion that its crew actively collaborated with human traffickers to facilitate illegal migration.
The charity, which has only been active for a year, declined to comment on the content of the detailed charges brought against them by Italian prosecutor Ambrogio Cartosio.
