"Only after we have gathered all the information and assessed the situation can we make an assessment of the allegations that are being made at this time".
The Italian authorities had been watching the boat of Jugend Rettet, the Iuventa, since October.
The crew is suspected of taking on board rubber boats full of migrants delivered directly to them by human traffickers and allowing the smugglers to escape in the boats, to be used again.
According to the prosecutor's files published by Italian media, at least one such encounter allegedly took place 1.3 miles off the Libyan coast.
The crew is suspected of disregarding the authority of the Italian coastguard, which oversees rescue operations in the area, more for humanitarian efforts than any other reason.
